There was confusion at the Nakuru Municipal mortuary when two families laid claim to the body of a girl who died in the Solai tragedy. According to Teresia Njeri, a survivor, her daughter, Mary Wambui, six, was washed away by the waters while they were in the house. ALSO READ:

DPP in Solai on fact finding mission Ms Njeri said she managed to identify the body of her daughter from several marks on her body. Another family identified the body as that of nine-year-old Mary Wanjiku, whose mother - Margaret Waithera, also died in the tragedy.